DESIGN NOTES


Problem 2: String Character Analysis — Design
Module Breakdown
Module 1: File Input Module

Prompts the user for a file path
Validates that the file exists and is accessible
Reads the entire file contents into a single string
Re-prompts on invalid file path

Module 2: Character Counting Module

Receives the string from the File Input Module
Initializes an array of 256 elements (one per extended ASCII character) to zero
Iterates through each character of the string
Increments the corresponding array index for each character encountered

Module 3: Top Three Analysis Module

Receives the populated count array from the Character Counting Module
Scans the array to find the three highest values
Handles ties by selecting the lower ASCII value first
Returns the three characters and their counts

Module 4: Undetected Count Module

Receives the populated count array from the Character Counting Module
Counts how many elements in the array remain at zero
Returns the total count of undetected characters

Module 5: String Reversal Module

Receives the original string from the File Input Module
Reverses the string character by character
Returns the reversed string

Module 6: Output Module

Receives data from the Top Three, Undetected Count, and String Reversal Modules
Displays the top three characters and their counts
Displays the number of undetected ASCII characters
Displays the reversed string

Data Flow
File Path → File Input Module → Character Counting Module → Top Three Analysis Module ─┐
                  │                        │                                            │
                  │                        └──→ Undetected Count Module ────────────────┤
                  │                                                                     │
                  └──→ String Reversal Module ─────────────────────────────────────────→ Output Module → User
Data Dictionary
VariableTypeDescriptionfilePathStringPath to the input filefileStringStringEntire contents of the file as a single stringcountArrayInteger Array [256]Occurrence count for each extended ASCII charactertopThreeArray of 3 PairsThree characters with highest counts and their valuesundetectedCountIntegerNumber of ASCII characters with zero occurrencesreversedStringStringThe file string in reverse order
Algorithm (Pseudocode)
FUNCTION getFileInput()
    PROMPT user for file path
    VALIDATE file exists
    READ entire file into fileString
    RETURN fileString

FUNCTION countCharacters(fileString)
    INITIALIZE countArray[256] to all zeros
    FOR each character in fileString
        index = ASCII value of character
        countArray[index] = countArray[index] + 1
    END FOR
    RETURN countArray

FUNCTION findTopThree(countArray)
    INITIALIZE topThree as empty array of 3 pairs
    FOR i = 0 to 255
        IF countArray[i] is greater than smallest value in topThree
            REPLACE smallest entry with (character i, countArray[i])
        END IF
    END FOR
    SORT topThree in descending order by count
    RETURN topThree

FUNCTION countUndetected(countArray)
    undetectedCount = 0
    FOR i = 0 to 255
        IF countArray[i] equals 0
            undetectedCount = undetectedCount + 1
        END IF
    END FOR
    RETURN undetectedCount

FUNCTION reverseString(fileString)
    reversedString = ""
    FOR i = length of fileString - 1 down to 0
        APPEND fileString[i] to reversedString
    END FOR
    RETURN reversedString

FUNCTION displayResults(topThree, undetectedCount, reversedString)
    PRINT topThree characters and counts
    PRINT undetectedCount
    PRINT reversedString
END FUNCTION

MAIN
    fileString = getFileInput()
    countArray = countCharacters(fileString)
    topThree = findTopThree(countArray)
    undetected = countUndetected(countArray)
    reversed = reverseString(fileString)
    displayResults(topThree, undetected, reversed)
END MAIN

